From: Dreeam <61569423+Dreeam-qwq@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 08:03:17 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Disable Grapheme Cluster Mode support

The Grapheme Cluster support detection has issues on some terminal, such as MCSM's emulated terminal

diff --git a/src/main/java/org/bukkit/craftbukkit/Main.java b/src/main/java/org/bukkit/craftbukkit/Main.java
index e6ea34b18c6db63efa77bb67d3484e4d66315ed6..b41c0741e6a6553449937241d919f1986eda1021 100644
--- a/src/main/java/org/bukkit/craftbukkit/Main.java
+++ b/src/main/java/org/bukkit/craftbukkit/Main.java
@@ -208,6 +208,7 @@ public class Main {
 
                 System.setProperty("library.jansi.version", "Paper"); // Paper - set meaningless jansi version to prevent git builds from crashing on Windows
                 System.setProperty("jdk.console", "java.base"); // Paper - revert default console provider back to java.base so we can have our own jline
+                System.setProperty("org.jline.terminal.graphemeCluster", "false"); // Leaf - Disable Grapheme Cluster mode support
 
                 io.papermc.paper.PaperBootstrap.boot(options);
             } catch (Throwable t) {
